                <head>122. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>The political crisis in Pakistan, which escalated into civil war in East Pakistan
                    in March 1971, ultimately led to armed conflict between India and Pakistan and
                    convulsed the subcontinent of South Asia through the end of the year. Most of
                    the important documents bearing on the United States response to that crisis are
                    in <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations, 1969–1976, South Asia Crisis, 1971.</hi>
                    The documents in this electronic publication for that period supplement, and
                    should be read in conjunction with, the printed volume.</p>
            </div>
